- By Geography: North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, South America, Middle East and Africa

Neonatal hypoxic-ischemic encephalopathy (NHIE) is a serious brain injury that occurs due to oxygen deprivation and limited blood flow to the brain, leading to significant neurological deficits in neonates. The global market for NHIE is segmented by type, treatment, end-user, and geography. The type segment includes neonatal encephalopathy and hypoxic-ischemic encephalopathy. The treatment options for NHIE consist of therapeutic hypothermia, medication, and other supportive therapies. End-users of NHIE products and services are hospitals, clinics, ambulatory surgical centers, and other healthcare facilities. Geographically, the market is divided into North America, Europe, Asia-Pacific, South America, and the Middle East and Africa.

